name: Alisa Orlova
about2: I took this background picture in Afghanistan, in the narrow corridor that separates the Pamirs from the Hindu Kush. There was almost no electricity, no shops, no running water except for streams, no phone connection - but many yaks. So many things have happened to me since then - gazing at the Maya ruins of El Mirador deep in the jungle of Peten, crossing the Takla Makan and the Tien Shan in rickety buses, tracking the incredibly rare snub-nosed monkeys near Shangri-La, climbing the 20000 ft Chachani volcano, to name just a few - but nothing can quite beat the evening  sun on the Hindu Kush. What does that have to do with my work as a blockchain content consultant? Perhaps nothing... or everything.
